{"type":"message","id":"d144d8dc","parentId":"450ab8e8","timestamp":"2026-04-21T19:54:42.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bupxzb8nfysq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**PRODUCT REQUIREMENT DOCUMENT**\n\n**SafeSight AI**\n\nAI-Powered Construction Site Safety Monitoring & Alert System\n\n| **Document Version** | 1.0                       |\n| -------------------- | ------------------------- |\n| **Status**           | Final Draft               |\n| **Date**             | April 2026                |\n| **Classification**   | Confidential              |\n| **Prepared by**      | SafeSight AI Product Team |\n\n# **1\\. Executive Summary**\n\nSafeSight AI is a full-stack, AI-driven construction site safety monitoring and alerting platform. The system leverages state-of-the-art computer vision and deep learning models (YOLOv8/v9, ResNet, EfficientDet) to continuously analyze live video feeds from existing IP cameras installed on construction sites. It automatically detects Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) compliance, identifies hazardous zone violations, recognizes dangerous behaviors, and delivers real-time multi-channel alerts to site supervisors, safety officers, and executive management.\n\nThe platform is designed as a complete production-ready product - not a prototype or MVP - covering the full software lifecycle from AI inference engine and edge computing layer to cloud backend, web/mobile management portal, analytics dashboard, ERP/BIM integrations, and regulatory compliance reporting.\n\n| **Key Value Proposition**                                                                                       |\n| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Reduce PPE non-compliance incidents by up to 85% through real-time AI detection and instant alerting            |\n| Lower construction site accident rates and associated costs (compensation, project delays, reputational damage) |\n| Provide evidence-based safety management with immutable audit trails for regulatory bodies                      |\n| Deliver ROI within 6-12 months by reducing insurance premiums, fines, and accident-related costs                |\n| Integrate seamlessly with existing camera infrastructure - no new hardware investment required                  |\n\n## **1.1 Problem Statement**\n\nConstruction sites remain among the most hazardous work environments globally. The construction sector accounts for approximately 20% of all fatal workplace injuries despite employing only around 7% of the workforce. The root causes are well documented:\n\n- Inconsistent PPE compliance - workers frequently remove helmets, high-visibility vests, and safety harnesses when unsupervised.\n- Inadequate hazard zone enforcement - restricted and danger zones are poorly enforced, especially on large, complex sites.\n- Reactive safety management - incidents are addressed after the fact, rather than prevented proactively.\n- Manual supervisor oversight - human supervisors cannot monitor every zone simultaneously and suffer from fatigue and attention drift.\n- Incomplete and retrospective reporting - safety reports are compiled manually and lack granularity or real-time visibility.\n\n## **1.2 Solution Overview**\n\nSafeSight AI addresses these challenges through a three-layer architecture: an edge AI inference layer (running on-site), a cloud processing and storage layer, and a client application layer (web portal and mobile apps). The system operates 24/7, processes video at up to 30 frames per second per camera, and delivers detection-to-alert latency under 3 seconds.\n\n# **2\\. Project Scope & Objectives**\n\n## **2.1 In Scope**\n\n- Real-time PPE detection: hard hat, safety vest (high-visibility), safety harness, safety gloves, safety boots, protective eyewear, face masks/respirators\n- Dangerous zone / geofencing violation detection and real-time alerts\n- Unsafe behavior recognition: using mobile phone while operating machinery, running in restricted areas, unauthorized climbing, workers entering under suspended loads\n- Crowd density monitoring and unsafe congregation detection\n- Fall detection and near-miss event detection\n- Fire and smoke detection (early warning)\n- Multi-site management from a single centralized dashboard\n- Role-based access control (RBAC): Super Admin, Site Manager, Safety Officer, Supervisor, Executive Viewer\n- Real-time alert delivery: in-app push notification, SMS, email, PA system integration, on-site siren/light beacon trigger\n- Comprehensive analytics: compliance trends, risk heatmaps, violation frequency, shift-level reporting\n- Video evidence management: auto-clip extraction, secure cloud storage, tamper-evident metadata\n- Regulatory compliance reporting: export to formats required by Vietnamese Ministry of Labour, OSHA, ISO 45001\n- REST API and webhook infrastructure for third-party integration (ERP, BIM, HR systems)\n- Mobile applications: iOS and Android (React Native) for supervisors and safety officers\n- Edge computing support: NVIDIA Jetson Orin, Intel NUC, standard x86 servers with GPU\n- On-premise deployment option for clients with data sovereignty requirements\n\n## **2.2 Out of Scope (Phase 1)**\n\n- Biometric identification of individual workers (facial recognition) - deferred to Phase 2 due to privacy regulation considerations\n- Autonomous drone surveillance integration - Phase 3 roadmap\n- AR/VR safety training modules - separate product line\n- Predictive accident modeling using historical big data - Phase 2 roadmap\n\n## **2.3 Strategic Objectives**\n\n| **#** | **Objective**               | **Success Metric**                  | **Target**   |\n| ----- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------- | ------------ |\n| O-01  | Maximize detection accuracy | PPE detection mAP@0.5               | \\>= 92%      |\n| O-02  | Minimize alert latency      | Detection-to-notification time      | < 3 seconds  |\n| O-03  | Ensure system reliability   | Platform uptime (annual)            | \\>= 99.5%    |\n| O-04  | Drive adoption              | Active sites within 12 months       | \\>= 50 sites |\n| O-05  | Demonstrate safety ROI      | Avg. client PPE violation reduction | \\>= 70%      |\n| O-06  | Support scale               | Cameras per deployment (max)        | \\>= 500      |\n| O-07  | Maintain compliance         | Reports passing regulatory audit    | 100%         |\n\n# **3\\. Stakeholders & User Personas**\n\n## **3.1 Stakeholder Map**\n\n| **Stakeholder**                  | **Role**               | **Primary Interest**                                     | **Engagement Level** |\n| -------------------------------- | ---------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------- |\n| Construction Company Executives  | Budget decision-makers | ROI, liability reduction, brand reputation               | High - sponsor       |\n| Site Safety Officers (HSE)       | Primary end users      | Real-time alerts, compliance reports, violation evidence | High - daily use     |\n| Site Supervisors / Foremen       | Operational end users  | Zone monitoring, team compliance, shift summaries        | High - daily use     |\n| IT/Infrastructure Teams          | Technical integrators  | API reliability, security, on-premise deployment         | Medium - integration |\n| Workers / Labour Force           | Subjects of monitoring | Fairness, privacy, non-punitive use                      | Low - indirect       |\n| Regulatory Bodies (MoLISA, OSHA) | Compliance authorities | Accurate audit trails, standardised reports              | Medium - compliance  |\n| Insurance Providers              | Risk assessors         | Incident data, compliance history                        | Low - reporting      |\n| SafeSight AI Ops Team            | Platform operators     | System health, AI model quality, support SLAs            | High - internal      |\n\n## **3.2 User Personas**\n\n### **Persona 1 - Nguyen Van An, Site Safety Officer (HSE Manager)**\n\n| **HSE Manager Profile**                                                                                                                          |\n| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| Age: 38 \\| Experience: 12 years in construction safety \\| Tech proficiency: Medium                                                               |\n| Primary device: Desktop in site office + Android smartphone on-site                                                                              |\n| Goals: Achieve zero lost-time injuries \\| Pass MoLISA quarterly inspections \\| Maintain documented evidence of all violations                    |\n| Pain points: Cannot watch all 40+ cameras simultaneously \\| Violation reports take 4 hours to compile manually \\| Workers ignore verbal warnings |\n| Needs from SafeSight AI: Instant mobile alerts when violations occur \\| One-click evidence download \\| Automated weekly compliance report        |\n\n### **Persona 2 - Tran Thi Bich, Executive Director (Construction Firm)**\n\n| **Executive Profile**                                                                                                                                |\n| ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Age: 52 \\| Experience: 20+ years in construction management \\| Tech proficiency: Low-Medium                                                          |\n| Primary device: iPad, minimal time on platform                                                                                                       |\n| Goals: Protect company from legal liability \\| Reduce accident-related insurance premiums \\| Win safety-certified project bids                       |\n| Pain points: Safety data is siloed and hard to interpret \\| No visibility into cross-site trends \\| Reactive - learns about incidents after the fact |\n| Needs from SafeSight AI: High-level executive dashboard \\| Cross-site KPI summaries \\| Monthly board-ready safety reports                            |\n\n### **Persona 3 - Pham Minh Duc, Site Foreman**\n\n| **Foreman Profile**                                                                                                                              |\n| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| Age: 29 \\| Experience: 5 years as foreman \\| Tech proficiency: Medium                                                                            |\n| Primary device: iPhone on-site                                                                                                                   |\n| Goals: Keep crew safe \\| Meet daily work targets without safety stoppages \\| Handle violations quickly without escalation                        |\n| Pain points: Workers remove PPE when hot/uncomfortable \\| Hard to enforce rules in remote corners of large sites \\| Paperwork is time-consuming  |\n| Needs from SafeSight AI: Instant push notifications with camera snapshot \\| Quick acknowledgement workflow \\| Worker violation history per shift |\n\n# **4\\. Functional Requirements**\n\n## **4.1 AI Detection Engine**\n\n### **4.1.1 PPE Detection Module**\n\nThe core detection pipeline uses a YOLOv8/v9 object detection backbone fine-tuned on a proprietary dataset of construction site imagery (minimum 150,000 annotated images across diverse lighting, weather, and PPE type conditions).\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**              | **Description**                                                                                                                                           | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| DET-001        | Hard Hat Detection       | Detect presence/absence of safety helmet per person bounding box. Distinguish between correct wearing and improper wearing (tilted, backward, on ground). | P0 - Critical |\n| DET-002        | Safety Vest Detection    | Detect high-visibility vest, reflective jacket. Flag missing or partially worn vest.                                                                      | P0 - Critical |\n| DET-003        | Safety Harness Detection | Detect full-body harness for workers at height (>2m). Detect harness-not-clipped events.                                                                  | P0 - Critical |\n| DET-004        | Protective Eyewear       | Detect safety glasses or goggles in relevant work zones (welding, grinding, chemical).                                                                    | P1 - High     |\n| DET-005        | Safety Gloves            | Detect gloves in high-risk manual tasks zone.                                                                                                             | P1 - High     |\n| DET-006        | Safety Footwear          | Detect safety boots vs. non-compliant footwear (sandals, trainers).                                                                                       | P1 - High     |\n| DET-007        | Respiratory Protection   | Detect dust masks, respirators in designated zones (demolition, concrete cutting).                                                                        | P1 - High     |\n| DET-008        | Multi-PPE Simultaneous   | Simultaneously detect all PPE items per worker in a single inference pass.                                                                                | P0 - Critical |\n| DET-009        | Compliance Score         | Calculate per-worker and per-zone PPE compliance score as a weighted percentage.                                                                          | P1 - High     |\n\n### **4.1.2 Hazard Zone & Geofencing Module**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**              | **Description**                                                                                                              | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| ZONE-001       | Virtual Geofence Drawing | Admin can draw polygon or rectangular restricted zones directly on the camera feed or floor plan. Up to 50 zones per camera. | P0 - Critical |\n| ZONE-002       | Real-Time Zone Violation | Detect when a person (or vehicle) enters a restricted zone. Trigger alert within 3 seconds.                                  | P0 - Critical |\n| ZONE-003       | Zone Scheduling          | Time-based zone activation (e.g., Zone A is restricted only during night shift). Full calendar scheduling.                   | P1 - High     |\n| ZONE-004       | Vehicle Proximity Alert  | Detect workers within a configurable radius of heavy machinery in motion.                                                    | P0 - Critical |\n| ZONE-005       | Suspended Load Zone      | Auto-define exclusion zone beneath crane lift operations. Trigger alert for any personnel entry.                             | P0 - Critical |\n| ZONE-006       | Zone Heatmap             | Generate time-lapse heatmap of zone violation frequency for weekly review.                                                   | P2 - Medium   |\n\n### **4.1.3 Behavior Recognition Module**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**           | **Description**                                                                                            | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| BEH-001        | Phone Use Detection   | Detect mobile phone usage by operator/worker in restricted-use zones.                                      | P1 - High     |\n| BEH-002        | Running Detection     | Detect running gait in restricted-speed zones.                                                             | P1 - High     |\n| BEH-003        | Fall Detection        | Detect sudden posture change indicative of a fall event. Trigger emergency alert.                          | P0 - Critical |\n| BEH-004        | Unauthorized Climbing | Detect climbing on scaffolding, structures, or equipment in non-designated areas.                          | P1 - High     |\n| BEH-005        | Crowd Density Alert   | Alert when the number of people in a zone exceeds a configured threshold.                                  | P1 - High     |\n| BEH-006        | Lone Worker Alert     | Alert when a single worker is detected alone in a high-risk zone for more than a configurable time period. | P1 - High     |\n| BEH-007        | Near-Miss Detection   | Detect close-call events (e.g., object narrowly missed, worker stumbled) for retrospective analysis.       | P2 - Medium   |\n\n### **4.1.4 Environmental Hazard Detection**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**                    | **Description**                                                                     | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| ENV-001        | Fire & Smoke Detection         | Computer vision smoke/flame detection as early-warning layer alongside IoT sensors. | P0 - Critical |\n| ENV-002        | Spill / Puddle Detection       | Detect liquid spills or standing water in walkway zones (slip hazard).              | P2 - Medium   |\n| ENV-003        | Debris / Obstruction Detection | Detect unsecured debris or materials in evacuation routes.                          | P2 - Medium   |\n\n## **4.2 Camera & Video Management**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**                  | **Description**                                                                                                     | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| CAM-001        | ONVIF Protocol Support       | Support all ONVIF-compliant IP cameras. Also support RTSP streams.                                                  | P0 - Critical |\n| CAM-002        | Camera Dashboard             | Grid view of all active camera feeds with live status indicators. Supports up to 500 cameras per installation.      | P0 - Critical |\n| CAM-003        | PTZ Camera Control           | Pan/Tilt/Zoom control from the web interface for supported cameras.                                                 | P1 - High     |\n| CAM-004        | Auto-Clip on Event           | Automatically extract and save 30-second video clip (15s pre-event + 15s post-event) upon every detected violation. | P0 - Critical |\n| CAM-005        | Continuous Recording         | Optional 24/7 continuous recording to cloud or NAS storage.                                                         | P1 - High     |\n| CAM-006        | Camera Health Monitoring     | Monitor feed connectivity, FPS drops, obstructed lens (AI-detected). Alert on camera failure.                       | P0 - Critical |\n| CAM-007        | Night Vision / IR Support    | Detection model variants optimised for IR and low-light camera feeds.                                               | P1 - High     |\n| CAM-008        | Multi-Camera Person Tracking | Track a single worker across multiple camera feeds using re-identification (ReID) model.                            | P2 - Medium   |\n\n## **4.3 Alert & Notification System**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**            | **Description**                                                                                                           | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| ALT-001        | In-App Real-Time Alert | Push notification within the web portal and mobile app. Include snapshot, violation type, camera ID, zone, and timestamp. | P0 - Critical |\n| ALT-002        | SMS Alert              | SMS delivery to pre-configured phone numbers per alert rule. Support Twilio and local VN SMS gateways.                    | P0 - Critical |\n| ALT-003        | Email Alert            | Formatted HTML email with embedded snapshot and violation details.                                                        | P1 - High     |\n| ALT-004        | PA System Integration  | Trigger on-site public address announcement via audio relay module upon critical violation.                               | P1 - High     |\n| ALT-005        | Siren / Beacon Trigger | Activate physical siren and/or flashing beacon via relay output for zone intrusion or fall events.                        | P0 - Critical |\n| ALT-006        | Alert Escalation       | If a violation alert is not acknowledged within N minutes, auto-escalate to a higher-authority contact.                   | P1 - High     |\n| ALT-007        | Alert Rules Engine     | Configurable rules: alert only on N consecutive violations within T seconds, per zone, per shift, per camera.             | P0 - Critical |\n| ALT-008        | Alert Suppression      | Suppress duplicate alerts for the same worker/zone within a configurable cool-down period.                                | P1 - High     |\n| ALT-009        | Webhook Outbound       | POST violation event payloads to customer-defined webhook endpoints for custom integrations.                              | P1 - High     |\n| ALT-010        | Alert Audit Log        | Immutable log of all alerts generated, delivered, acknowledged, and escalated with user and timestamp.                    | P0 - Critical |\n\n## **4.4 Dashboard & Analytics**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**                     | **Description**                                                                                                      | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| DASH-001       | Executive Summary Dashboard     | Top-level KPIs: total violations today, compliance rate, open incidents, active sites. Single-screen for executives. | P0 - Critical |\n| DASH-002       | Site Operations Dashboard       | Per-site live view: camera grid, active alerts, zone status, current worker count. Primary view for site managers.   | P0 - Critical |\n| DASH-003       | Compliance Trend Charts         | Time-series charts of PPE compliance rate by day/week/month. Filterable by site, zone, shift, PPE type.              | P0 - Critical |\n| DASH-004       | Violation Frequency Heatmap     | Geographic heatmap overlay on site floor plan showing violation hotspots.                                            | P1 - High     |\n| DASH-005       | Shift Comparison Report         | Side-by-side compliance comparison across shifts (morning/afternoon/night) to identify risk patterns.                | P1 - High     |\n| DASH-006       | Worker Violation History        | Per-worker violation log (identified by helmet ID tag or re-ID). Supports disciplinary workflow.                     | P2 - Medium   |\n| DASH-007       | Incident Investigation Timeline | Reconstruct event sequence with linked video clips, alert logs, and detection metadata for post-incident review.     | P1 - High     |\n| DASH-008       | Custom Report Builder           | Drag-and-drop report builder with configurable date range, metrics, and output format (PDF, Excel, CSV).             | P1 - High     |\n| DASH-009       | Scheduled Report Delivery       | Auto-generate and email reports on a configurable schedule (daily, weekly, monthly).                                 | P1 - High     |\n| DASH-010       | Regulatory Export               | Export reports in formats compliant with Vietnamese MoLISA forms, OSHA 300 log, ISO 45001 clause mapping.            | P0 - Critical |\n\n## **4.5 User & Access Management**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**                | **Description**                                                                                                            | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| USR-001        | RBAC System                | Five standard roles: Super Admin, Organization Admin, Site Manager, Safety Officer, Supervisor. Custom roles configurable. | P0 - Critical |\n| USR-002        | SSO Integration            | Support SAML 2.0 and OAuth 2.0 for enterprise SSO (Microsoft Entra ID, Google Workspace).                                  | P1 - High     |\n| USR-003        | Two-Factor Authentication  | Mandatory TOTP-based 2FA for all admin and safety officer accounts.                                                        | P0 - Critical |\n| USR-004        | User Activity Audit Log    | Log all user actions (login, configuration change, video access, report export) with timestamp and IP.                     | P0 - Critical |\n| USR-005        | Session Management         | Configurable session timeout, concurrent login policy, force logout capability.                                            | P1 - High     |\n| USR-006        | Granular Permission Matrix | Control access at the level of individual camera, zone, site, and report type per user.                                    | P1 - High     |\n\n## **4.6 Integration & API Layer**\n\n| **Feature ID** | **Feature**               | **Description**                                                                                                                       | **Priority**  |\n| -------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |\n| API-001        | RESTful API (v1)          | Full REST API covering all platform objects: sites, cameras, violations, alerts, users, reports. OpenAPI 3.0 specification published. | P0 - Critical |\n| API-002        | Webhook Subscriptions     | Subscribe to event types (violation_detected, alert_escalated, camera_offline). Retry logic with exponential backoff.                 | P0 - Critical |\n| API-003        | ERP Integration Connector | Pre-built connectors for SAP, Oracle, and Microsoft Dynamics for safety incident ingestion.                                           | P2 - Medium   |\n| API-004        | BIM Integration           | Overlay violation data and zone definitions on IFC/BIM models. Revit and Navisworks plugin.                                           | P2 - Medium   |\n| API-005        | HR System Integration     | Sync worker roster for violation-to-worker assignment and disciplinary workflow.                                                      | P2 - Medium   |\n| API-006        | IoT Sensor Integration    | Ingest data from gas sensors, temperature sensors, and wearable IoT devices for correlated alerting.                                  | P2 - Medium   |\n| API-007        | Video Export API          | Programmatic access to violation clip library. Signed URL delivery with expiry for secure downstream use.                             | P1 - High     |\n\n# **5\\. Non-Functional Requirements**\n\n## **5.1 Performance Requirements**\n\n| **ID**   | **Requirement**             | **Target**                                                              |\n| -------- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| PERF-001 | AI Inference Latency (edge) | < 100ms per frame per camera stream at 1080p                            |\n| PERF-002 | Detection-to-Alert Delivery | < 3 seconds end-to-end from violation event to notification receipt     |\n| PERF-003 | Concurrent Camera Streams   | Single edge node processes >= 16 x 1080p streams at 15 FPS              |\n| PERF-004 | Dashboard Load Time         | < 2 seconds initial load; < 500ms subsequent page transitions           |\n| PERF-005 | API Response Time           | P95 response time < 200ms for all read endpoints under normal load      |\n| PERF-006 | Report Generation           | < 30 seconds for reports covering up to 90-day range and 100 cameras    |\n| PERF-007 | Video Clip Retrieval        | Signed URL available for clip download < 5 seconds after request        |\n| PERF-008 | Maximum Cameras / Platform  | \\>= 5,000 cameras across all deployments on shared cloud infrastructure |\n\n## **5.2 Reliability & Availability**\n\n| **ID**  | **Requirement**          | **Target**                                                                                      |\n| ------- | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| REL-001 | Platform Uptime SLA      | \\>= 99.5% measured monthly (< 3.6 hours downtime/month)                                         |\n| REL-002 | Edge Node Resilience     | Edge node continues local detection and buffering for >= 72 hours if cloud connectivity is lost |\n| REL-003 | Alert Delivery Guarantee | Alert delivery success rate >= 99.9% (retry logic + fallback channels)                          |\n| REL-004 | Data Durability          | Video evidence and violation records stored with >= 99.999999999% (11 nines) durability         |\n| REL-005 | Graceful Degradation     | If AI inference is overloaded, system queues frames and alerts operator - never silently drops  |\n| REL-006 | RTO                      | Recovery Time Objective: < 1 hour for full platform restoration after major incident            |\n| REL-007 | RPO                      | Recovery Point Objective: < 5 minutes data loss in disaster recovery scenario                   |\n\n## **5.3 Security Requirements**\n\n| **ID**  | **Requirement**          | **Detail**                                                                                                        |\n| ------- | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| SEC-001 | Encryption in Transit    | TLS 1.3 for all API, WebSocket, and dashboard communications. SRTP for RTSP streams.                              |\n| SEC-002 | Encryption at Rest       | AES-256 encryption for all stored video, violation records, and configuration data.                               |\n| SEC-003 | Penetration Testing      | Annual third-party penetration test. Critical findings remediated within 14 days.                                 |\n| SEC-004 | Vulnerability Management | CVE scanning on all container images in CI/CD pipeline. No Critical/High CVEs in production.                      |\n| SEC-005 | API Authentication       | OAuth 2.0 Bearer tokens with short expiry (15 min access token, 7-day refresh token).                             |\n| SEC-006 | Data Privacy             | Compliance with Vietnamese Decree 13/2023/ND-CP on personal data protection. No biometric data stored in Phase 1. |\n| SEC-007 | Network Isolation        | Edge node communicates with cloud via VPN tunnel. Camera VLAN isolated from corporate network.                    |\n| SEC-008 | Audit Logging            | All administrative actions and data access logged to immutable append-only store (WORM).                          |\n\n## **5.4 Scalability Requirements**\n\n- Horizontal auto-scaling of inference workers, API services, and stream processors via Kubernetes (K8s) HPA.\n- AI model serving layer supports GPU-accelerated nodes (NVIDIA A10/A100) for cloud inference.\n- Message queue architecture (Apache Kafka) for decoupled, high-throughput event processing.\n- Database: PostgreSQL with read replicas; TimescaleDB for time-series violation metrics; Redis for session and cache.\n- Object storage: S3-compatible (AWS S3 or MinIO for on-premise) with automated tiered lifecycle policies.\n- Multi-region support: Primary region Vietnam (AWS ap-southeast-1); DR region Singapore.\n\n# **6\\. System Architecture**\n\n## **6.1 Architecture Overview**\n\nSafeSight AI is built on a three-tier architecture comprising the Edge Layer, Cloud Backend Layer, and Client Application Layer. All tiers communicate over encrypted channels and are designed for independent horizontal scaling.\n\n## **6.2 Edge Layer (On-Site Hardware)**\n\n### **6.2.1 Edge Node Specifications**\n\n| **Component**     | **Specification**                                                             | **Purpose**                     |\n| ----------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |\n| Primary Hardware  | NVIDIA Jetson AGX Orin 64GB or equivalent x86 server with NVIDIA RTX 4000 GPU | AI inference, stream processing |\n| OS                | Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (headless)                                                   | Edge OS base                    |\n| Inference Runtime | TensorRT 8.x, ONNX Runtime with CUDA                                          | Optimized model execution       |\n| Stream Ingestor   | GStreamer pipeline + custom Python orchestrator                               | RTSP stream handling            |\n| Local Storage     | 2TB NVMe SSD (RAID-1)                                                         | 30-day local video buffer       |\n| Connectivity      | 1 Gbps LAN + 4G LTE failover                                                  | Cloud sync and alert delivery   |\n| Watchdog Service  | Systemd + custom health-check daemon                                          | Auto-restart on failure         |\n\n### **6.2.2 Edge Processing Pipeline**\n\n- RTSP streams ingested per camera via GStreamer.\n- Frames decoded and batched at configurable FPS (default: 10 FPS, up to 30 FPS).\n- Batched frames passed to TensorRT-optimized YOLOv8 inference engine.\n- Detection bounding boxes and class labels output per frame.\n- Post-processing module applies NMS, confidence thresholding, and tracking (ByteTrack algorithm).\n- Rule engine evaluates detections against configured zone rules and PPE requirements.\n- Violation events published to local Kafka broker for guaranteed delivery.\n- Events forwarded to cloud backend via gRPC over VPN. Buffered locally on connectivity loss.\n- Violation video clip extracted and uploaded to cloud object storage asynchronously.\n\n## **6.3 Cloud Backend Layer**\n\n| **Service**              | **Technology**                    | **Responsibility**                                |\n| ------------------------ | --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |\n| API Gateway              | AWS API Gateway + Kong            | Rate limiting, auth, routing, load balancing      |\n| Core API Service         | Python FastAPI (async)            | Business logic, CRUD, report generation           |\n| Event Processing Service | Apache Kafka + Kafka Streams      | Real-time violation event ingestion and fanout    |\n| Alert Dispatch Service   | Celery + Redis (async workers)    | Multi-channel alert delivery with retry logic     |\n| AI Training Pipeline     | MLflow + PyTorch + AWS SageMaker  | Model retraining, versioning, A/B evaluation      |\n| Video Storage            | AWS S3 + CloudFront CDN           | Secure violation clip storage and delivery        |\n| Primary Database         | PostgreSQL 15 (RDS) + TimescaleDB | Relational data, time-series metrics              |\n| Cache Layer              | Redis 7 Cluster                   | Session, frequently-accessed configs, rate limits |\n| Search / Audit Log       | OpenSearch (AWS)                  | Full-text search on logs; WORM audit trail        |\n| Container Orchestration  | Kubernetes (EKS) + Helm           | Service deployment, scaling, health management    |\n| Observability            | Prometheus + Grafana + PagerDuty  | Metrics, dashboards, on-call alerting             |\n\n## **6.4 Client Application Layer**\n\n| **Application**      | **Technology**                       | **Key Capabilities**                                                            |\n| -------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Web Portal (Primary) | React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS | Full platform management, dashboards, analytics, configuration, video review    |\n| iOS App              | React Native (Expo) + Swift modules  | Real-time alerts, mobile camera view, incident acknowledgement, field reporting |\n| Android App          | React Native (Expo) + Kotlin modules | Same as iOS; FCM push notifications; offline capability for alert history       |\n| Edge Admin Console   | Vue 3 (local, no internet required)  | On-site edge node configuration, camera management, local health monitoring     |\n\n# **7\\. AI Model Specifications**\n\n## **7.1 Detection Models**\n\n| **Model**           | **Architecture**              | **Dataset**                                    | **mAP@0.5 Target**   | **Inference (ms)** |\n| ------------------- | ----------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------ |\n| PPE Detector        | YOLOv8-L fine-tuned           | 150K+ annotated construction images, augmented | \\>= 92%              | < 40ms (TRT)       |\n| Behavior Recognizer | YOLOv8-Pose + LSTM classifier | 50K+ action sequences, 15 behavior classes     | \\>= 85%              | < 60ms (TRT)       |\n| Zone Monitor        | YOLOv8-M + centroid tracker   | Shared with PPE detector                       | \\>= 95% (person det) | < 30ms (TRT)       |\n| Fire/Smoke Detector | EfficientDet-D2 fine-tuned    | 30K fire/smoke images + synthetic              | \\>= 90%              | < 50ms (TRT)       |\n| Person Re-ID        | ResNet50-IBN + PCB head       | Market-1501 + custom site dataset              | Rank-1 >= 88%        | < 20ms (TRT)       |\n\n## **7.2 Model Training & Continuous Improvement**\n\n- Training Infrastructure: AWS SageMaker with NVIDIA A100 GPU instances.\n- Data Annotation Pipeline: LabelStudio annotation platform with QA review workflow. All annotations validated by senior annotators.\n- Dataset Versioning: DVC (Data Version Control) for full dataset reproducibility.\n- Model Registry: MLflow model registry with staging / production promotion workflow.\n- Active Learning Loop: Low-confidence detections from production are automatically queued for human review and re-annotation to continuously improve model quality.\n- Retraining Frequency: Scheduled monthly retraining + ad-hoc retraining triggered by mAP degradation alerts.\n- A/B Evaluation: New model versions are shadow-deployed against production traffic before full promotion. Promotion requires demonstrating >= 1% mAP improvement on holdout set.\n- Bias Monitoring: Model performance is evaluated across sub-groups (time of day, weather condition, PPE colour variations) to detect and mitigate performance disparities.\n\n## **7.3 Model Explainability**\n\n- Grad-CAM heatmap visualizations available for any detection event in the web portal, allowing safety officers to understand what the AI analyzed.\n- Confidence scores displayed alongside all detections and violation events.\n- Per-class precision/recall metrics published on a public model card updated with each release.\n\n# **8\\. Data Management & Privacy**\n\n## **8.1 Data Classification**\n\n| **Data Type**                               | **Classification** | **Retention Policy**                  | **Storage Location**     |[... 18478 more characters truncated]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776801282361}}
