{"type":"message","id":"d573b99c","parentId":"486e1e39","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:13:01.861Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the CLAUDE.md for non-coding agents in English, not Vietnamese. Let me update all the non-coding agents with English version.","thinkingSignature":"328d31cd74813e882d1f4402a46af23c9c939e5aa2ee1ed94826d8a5e0a2dcc5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2rs9hwlx2had_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat << 'EOF' > /tmp/fix_claude.sh\n#!/bin/bash\n\nCLAUDE_EN=\"# CLAUDE.md\n\nBehavioral guidelines to reduce common LLM mistakes for non-coding agents.\n\n## 1. Think Before Acting\n\n- State your assumptions explicitly. If uncertain, ask.\n- If multiple interpretations exist, present them - don't pick silently.\n- If a simpler approach exists, say so. Push back when warranted.\n- If something is unclear, stop. Name what's confusing. Ask.\n\n## 2. Simplicity First\n\nMinimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.\n\n- No features beyond what was asked.\n- No abstractions for single-use items.\n- No 'flexibility' or 'configurability' that wasn't requested.\n- If you write 200 lines when 50 would do, rewrite.\n\n## 3. Minimum Changes\n\nTouch only what you must.\n\n- Don't 'improve' adjacent content.\n- Don't refactor things that aren't broken.\n- Match existing style, even if you'd do it differently.\n\n## 4. Clear Success Criteria\n\nDefine success criteria. Loop until verified.\n\nTask → Verifiable goal:\n- 'Analyze PRD' → 'Create SPEC.md with verified checklist'\n- 'Write documentation' → 'Document reviewed by user'\n\n## 5. Non-Coding Specific\n\n- When creating specs/docs: always have clear structure, include TOC\n- When spawning agents: define specific tasks, include deliverable checklist\n- When researching: cite sources, use bullet points\n- When writing reports: executive summary first, details after\n\n## 6. Confirmation Loop\n\nFor new requests:\n1. Clarify → confirm with user\n2. Plan → brief steps\n3. Execute → verify\n4. Report → results + next steps\n\"\n\nBASE=\"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review\"\n\nNON_CODING_AGENTS=(\n    \"master-orchestrator\"\n    \"planner\"\n    \"prompt-optimizer\"\n    \"agile-product-owner\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-agile\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-architect\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-product-strategy\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-pm\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-content\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-seo\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-seo-audit\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-content-engine\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-content-strategy\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-docs\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-epic\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-market\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-review\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-ui-design\"\n    \"ahv-dtlx-ui-ux\"\n    \"ai-seo\"\n    \"article-writing\"\n    \"deep-research\"\n    \"documentation-lookup\"\n    \"epic-design\"\n    \"harness-optimizer\"\n    \"market-intelligence\"\n    \"performance-optimizer\"\n    \"product-marketing-context\"\n    \"product-strategy\"\n    \"realistic-seeder\"\n    \"seo-audit\"\n    \"stitch-design\"\n    \"content-engine\"\n    \"content-strategy\"\n)\n\nfor agent in \"${NON_CODING_AGENTS[@]}\"; do\n    agent_dir=\"$BASE/$agent\"\n    if [ -d \"$agent_dir\" ]; then\n        echo \"$CLAUDE_EN\" > \"$agent_dir/CLAUDE.md\"\n        echo \"✓ $agent - updated to English\"\n    fi\ndone\n\necho \"Done!\"\nEOF\nchmod +x /tmp/fix_claude.sh\n/tmp/fix_claude.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":795,"cacheRead":51005,"cacheWrite":2818,"totalTokens":54618,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776820360084,"responseId":"0637538966636c5b49b24abcaf6fa1d5"}}
