{"type":"message","id":"48899cdc","parentId":"29d6124b","timestamp":"2026-04-22T05:28:17.270Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The structure is correct. The pages are organized with \"AHV CMS Teacher - Đào tạo lái xe\" as the parent. But I notice that \"5.1\", \"5.2\", \"5.3\" should be children of \"5. QUẢN LÝ HỌC VIÊN\" - let me check if they were created correctly. It seems the parent-child relationship isn't being picked up properly - all pages are direct children of the root page.\n\nWait, looking at the output more carefully - it shows all pages as direct children of the root, not nested properly. This is because the parent_id lookup happened before the parent page was created, so all pages were created as root pages.\n\nLet me fix this by running the script again or creating a new version that properly handles the hierarchy. But actually, looking at the Confluence output, it seems the pages ARE properly nested (they show the correct parent), so this might just be a display issue in my check.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the output - the output shows \"AHV CMS Teacher - Đào tạo lái xe → 5.1. DANH SÁCH KHÓA HỌC\" which means 5.1 is a child of the main page. This is correct!\n\nBut wait - 5.1 should be a child of 5 (QUẢN LÝ HỌC VIÊN), not directly under the root. Let me verify by looking at the actual content of one page to make sure the format is correct.","thinkingSignature":"19be683a1a2c941cab5c593639d2b1c6acc5d59bb3472d39a25b11a288d0e419"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b50g024fu3ik_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check content format of a page\ncurl -s \"https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/$(curl -s 'https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/space/AHVTEACHER/content?limit=20' -u 'ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com:ATATT3xFfGF0bFjmIN6IPHwDzRChO8oMe5XAaA6dheluE8J2eUTNZHLgprik7oLx-vNnZsNVCb4cAAjziLDb27lKFHU2_RTgdeuv8zMkaPR-or2gSJQjHp8TMmOtI53F6MauTeaXX5Tg4gdMYyJ2nUKI-2HSMvK4TLkXLmKSKrdGrOpNDLRgMxA=8865492F' | python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(p['id']) for p in d.get('page',{}).get('results',[]) if p['title']=='4. QUẢN LÝ GIÁO VIÊN']\\\")?expand=body.storage\" \\\n  -u \"ninhkhuongpl7@gmail.com:ATATT3xFfGF0bFjmIN6IPHwDzRChO8oMe5XAaA6dheluE8J2eUTNZHLgprik7oLx-vNnZsNVCb4cAAjziLDb27lKFHU2_RTgdeuv8zMkaPR-or2gSJQjHp8TMmOtI53F6MauTeaXX5Tg4gdMYyJ2nUKI-2HSMvK4TLkXLmKSKrdGrOpNDLRgMxA=8865492F\" | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys,re\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint('Title:', d.get('title'))\nbody = d.get('body',{}).get('storage',{}).get('value','')\n# Check for key elements\nprint('Has metadata table:', 'Target Release' in body)\nprint('Has TOC:', 'toc' in body)\nprint('Has VERSION CONTROL:', 'VERSION CONTROL' in body)\nprint('Has DESCRIPTION:', 'I. DESCRIPTION' in body)\nprint('Has UI DESCRIPTION:', 'UI DESCRIPTION' in body)\nprint('Has status macros:', 'status' in body)\nprint('---')\nprint('Content preview (first 1500 chars):')\nimport html\ntext = re.sub('<[^>]+>', ' ', body)\ntext = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\nprint(text[:1500])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":424,"output":938,"cacheRead":56503,"cacheWrite":854,"totalTokens":58719,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776835683475,"responseId":"06378f64750f47ab2e2bcc19c2885dbf"}}
